; O-word subroutine return-value semantics.
; Classic verified this.return_value / this.value_returned via inline ;py,
; asserts; gomc has no embedded Python, so we make #<_value> observable in the
; canon stream via a rapid move after each call and check the values.

; return a value via endsub
o<function1> sub
o<function1> endsub [4711]

; return a value via return
o<function2> sub
o100 return [4712]
o<function2> endsub

; a procedure without return value
o<proc> sub
o<proc> endsub

; before any call the return value is 0
g0 x#<_value>

o<function1> call
g0 x#<_value>          ; 4711 — set via endsub

o<proc> call
g0 x#<_value>          ; 0 — cleared after a no-return sub

o<function2> call
g0 x#<_value>          ; 4712 — set via return

o<proc> call
g0 x#<_value>          ; 0 — cleared again

m2
